Subject:Re: [child_lit] Libraries damaged by Sandy?
Along the same lines (forgive me if I've posted this before, but it bears repeating): The Society of Children's Book Writers and Illustrators offers grants to areas hit by natural disasters to provide relief to libraries, schools, etc. SCBWI is an international organization; the first relief grant was awarded in Japan after the earthquake and tsunami.

To request a grant, write to your area's Regional Advisor (find her/him at http://www.scbwi.org/Pages.aspx/Regional-Chapters). You do not have to be an SCBWI member.

Tracy


Tracy Barrett, US Regional Advisor Coordinator, SCBWI
Dark of the Moon "deft, dark, and enthralling" (School Library Journal)
